data.title: AI-powered mobile clinics in rural India improve breast cancer screening. NVIDIA & MedCognetics partner to provide healthcare to underserved areas.
data.description: NVIDIA has partnered with MedCognetics to provide AI-enhanced breast cancer screenings through mobile clinics, aiming to offer vital healthcare services to underserved regions in India. This collaboration combines NVIDIA's advanced technology with MedCognetics' medical expertise to improve early detection rates. The initiative is set to reach a significant number of individuals in need, potentially saving lives by diagnosing breast cancer at earlier stages.

data.title: Trust Stamp to exchange warrants with institutional investor, likely generating $4.3 million before expenses.
data.description: Trust Stamp, a global provider of AI-powered identity services, has reached a warrant inducement agreement with an institutional investor for the exercise of outstanding warrants issued in September 2024, December 2024, and January 2025. The investor will exercise warrants to purchase 413,696 shares at $4.83 per share from September 2024 and 621,303 shares at $8.45 per share from January 2025 after the exercise prices were reduced to $4.20 per share. Additionally, all outstanding December 2024 warrants will be exchanged for new warrants. The total gross proceeds from the exercise of warrants are projected to be around $4.3 million before placement agent fees and offering expenses are deducted.

data.title: Bitcoin's 17th anniversary sees BTC bouncing to $109,000, up from a $207,000 market cap in 2010 to almost $2 trillion.
data.description: On the 17th anniversary of the Bitcoin White Paper, the price of Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC) soared to $109,000. Originally created by Satoshi Nakamoto, Bitcoin started with a market cap of $207,000 in 2010 and has now reached nearly $2 trillion. Despite hitting a record high of $126,000, the price has since retreated as some investors view the dip as a buying opportunity. The current sentiment towards Bitcoin has turned cautious as it consolidates its position. Jeff Park, an advisor at Bitwise, shared insights on the market trends. data.title: MGM Resorts' mixed earnings: 24 cents EPS (missed 40-cent target), revenue $4.25B (beat $4.23B exp), China sales up 17%. Vegas sales down 7%.
data.description: MGM Resorts International recently reported mixed third-quarter results, with adjusted earnings per share at 24 cents, falling short of analyst expectations of 40 cents. However, revenue of $4.25 billion exceeded estimates and marked a 2% increase from the previous year. MGM China saw significant growth with $1.1 billion in sales (a 17% increase) and record adjusted EBITDA. The Las Vegas unit, on the other hand, experienced a 7% decline in sales due to hotel room renovations. Despite these challenges, MGM stock dropped over 3% in the past five sessions and nearly 8% in the last month, pointing to potential trading opportunities spurred by the company's volatility. You can read the full article on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Court orders Trump admin to pay SNAP benefits during shutdown to prevent millions of low-income Americans from losing support.
data.description: Lawsuits have been filed by states, cities, and nonprofits in an effort to prevent the termination of benefits for millions of low-income Americans. The Trump administration announced they would halt funding for these benefits, set to begin on Saturday. This action has sparked legal challenges aimed at safeguarding those at risk of losing essential support.

data.title: Zcash's price surged over 800%, hitting $373 and surpassing Monero in value. The market cap reached $6.2 billion, leading in privacy coins. Arthur Hayes predicts it could hit $10,000.
data.description: Zcash (ZEC) saw a significant surge of over 8% on Friday, reaching approximately $373 and achieving an eight-year high. This increase made it the most valuable privacy-focused cryptocurrency, surpassing Monero (XMR). The market capitalization of Zcash reached $6.2 billion, surpassing Monero and solidifying its position in the privacy coin sector. ZEC's price has risen by more than 45% in the last week and has recorded an increase of over 800% since early October. This growth is notable as the broader cryptocurrency market has been in a consolidation phase. Privacy coins like Zcash and Monero offer anonymity by obscuring sender, receiver, and transaction data, which Bitcoin (BTC) does not provide. With increasing regulatory scrutiny on blockchain transparency, investors are showing interest in tokens that maintain transaction privacy. The surge in Zcash's value was accelerated by predictions made by BitMEX co-founder Arthur Hayes, who suggested that Zcash could potentially rally to $10,000, referring to it as a significant rotation play in the market. ZEC's price climbed from $272 in response to this prediction.
